# Copyright and File Header Requirements

## 1. Doxygen File Header Format

**REQUIRED**: Include a Doxygen file header at the top of every source file.

### C++ Header Files (`.hpp`)
```cpp
/**
 * @file filename.hpp
 * @author Author Name (email@example.com)
 * @brief Brief description of the file
 * @version 0.1
 * @date YYYY-MM-DD
 *
 * @copyright Copyright (c) YYYY Boyle Development Team
 *            All rights reserved.
 *
 */

#pragma once
```

### C++ Source Files (`.cpp`)
```cpp
/**
 * @file filename.cpp
 * @author Author Name (email@example.com)
 * @brief Brief description of the file
 * @version 0.1
 * @date YYYY-MM-DD
 *
 * @copyright Copyright (c) YYYY Boyle Development Team
 *            All rights reserved.
 *
 */
```

### CMake Files (`CMakeLists.txt`)
CMake files do not require a file header.

## 2. Rules
- Use the current year when creating new files
- Place the Doxygen file header before any other content (including `#pragma once`)
- **REQUIRED**: Include exactly one blank line between the file header and `#pragma once`
- Use exactly this format - all fields (`@file`, `@author`, `@brief`, `@version`, `@date`, `@copyright`) are required

## 3. Exceptions
- **`.mdc` rule files**: YAML frontmatter (`---`) MUST be at line 1 for Cursor to parse. Omit copyright in `.mdc` files.
- **CMake files**: No header required.
